description: Look at the lamp for any sign of damage or improper installation., outcome="NOMINAL\n\nFeedback:\nThe visual inspection of the Main Load (lamp) was completed successfully. The bulb is lit, and there are no observable internal faults reported (specifically, no evidence of burned filaments or improper installation was detected during this step). Although the simulation note indicates instability or oscillation in the circuit, this relates to circuit behavior rather than to the bulb itself. The physical condition of the lamp appears nominal based on the observations provided.\n\nRecommendation: For further diagnosis, address the circuit's unstable state separately, as no lamp-specific anomalies have been detected at this stage.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Battery,
description: Use a voltimeter to test the battery energy content, outcome='ANOMALOUS\n\nFeedback:\n\nThe voltage measurement at the battery terminals reads 12.0 V (positive) and 0.0 V (negative), which nominally suggests that the battery is providing a typical expected voltage and does not appear to be depleted from the voltage reading alone. However, a critical warning is present: "[NOTE: The simulation did not converge — the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state.]" \n\nThis anomalous simulation behavior could suggest one of the following:\n\n- The battery or some other circuit element may be damaged or intermittently failing, leading to instability when attempting to operate or measure the circuit.\n- There may be external issues (e.g., wiring faults, oscillations, or component failures) affecting the battery or entire circuit that merit further investigation.\n\n**Immediate Recommendation:**\n- Double-check all physical connections and battery integrity (visual inspection for swelling, leakage, or overheating).\n- Attempt to measure battery voltage outside the circuit to rule out circuit-induced anomalies.\n- Investigate further for the underlying cause of simulation instability, as this could mask issues such as intermittent battery failure (BatteryDamaged) even though static voltage appears normal.\n\nLet me know if you repeat the measurement or have further results.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
